issue.title: Error recovery from Sass errors
issue.body:
# 🐛 bug report

As I start typing in the scss file , I immediately get this error and it happens everytime:

```
🚨 Build failed.

@parcel/transformer-sass: expected "{".
╷
289 │ .
│  ^
```

And parcel stops to function, i need to close it and npm start all over again.




## 🎛 Configuration (.babelrc, package.json, cli command)
```
{
  "name": "ime-cadastru",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "source": "./src/pages/cadastru.html",
  "description": "",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "parcel ./src/index.html",
    "build": "parcel build"
  },
  "keywords": [],
  "author": "",
  "license": "ISC",
  "devDependencies": {
    "@parcel/transformer-sass": "^2.0.1",
    "parcel": "^2.0.1",
    "sass": "^1.43.4",
    "sharp": "^0.29.3"
  }
}
```



## 🔦 Context

<!--- How has this issue affected you? What are you trying to accomplish? -->

I try to write css in the scss files and immediatly after i start typing i get this error.



## 💻 Code Sample

<!-- Please provide a code repository, gist, code snippet, or sample files to reproduce the issue -->

## 🌍 Your Environment

<!--- Include as many relevant details about the environment you experienced the bug in -->

| Software         | Version(s) |
| ---------------- | ---------- |
| Parcel "@parcel/transformer-sass": "^2.0.1",

    "sass": "^1.43.4",

issue.title: unknown Statement of type "ForOfStatement"
issue.body:
🐛 bug report

### 🎛 Configuration (.babelrc, package.json, cli command)

package.json
```js
{
    "scripts": {
        "dev": "parcel ./src/index.html -d build/ --target=browser"
    }
}
```

.babelrc
```js
{
    "presets": ["react"],
    "plugins": ["react-hot-loader/babel"]
}
```

### 🤔 Expected Behavior

It bundles and transpiles my es6 targetting node_module dependencies

### 😯 Current Behavior

regenerator-transform fails because it finds a for-of statement within a generator.
```
×  C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\@private\core\dist\iterables.js: C:/git/my_webapp/node_modules/@private/core/dist/iterables.js: unknown Statement of type "ForOfStatement"
    at Emitter.Ep.explodeStatement (C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\regenerator-transform\lib\emit.js:648:13)
    at C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\regenerator-transform\lib\emit.js:344:12
    at Array.forEach (<anonymous>)
    at Emitter.Ep.explodeStatement (C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\regenerator-transform\lib\emit.js:343:22)
    at Emitter.Ep.explode (C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\regenerator-transform\lib\emit.js:298:40)
    at PluginPass.exit (C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\regenerator-transform\lib\visit.js:122:15)
    at newFn (C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\babel-traverse\lib\visitors.js:276:21)
    at NodePath._call (C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\babel-traverse\lib\path\context.js:76:18)
    at NodePath.call (C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\babel-traverse\lib\path\context.js:48:17)
    at NodePath.visit (C:\git\my_webapp\node_modules\babel-traverse\lib\path\context.js:117:8)
```

### 💁 Possible Solution

According to https://github.com/facebook/regenerator/issues/229 for-of statements need to be transformed before regenerator-transform can be applied. Maybe there is a way to force this.

### 🌍 Your Environment

| Software         | Version(s) |
| ---------------- | ---------- |
| Parcel           | 1.7.1 |
| Node             | 9.11.1 |
| npm/Yarn         | 1.6.0 |
| Operating System | Win 7 64bit |

comment.body: Adding "babel-plugin-transform-es2015-for-of": "^6.23.0" in package.json and compiling it first worked

I think a big problem is that this actually mutates the asset graph, so running `BundleGraph.fromAssetGraph` multiple times isn't safe (which would happen in watch mode).

So at least it should be something like this: https://github.com/parcel-bundler/parcel/commit/908467af6149a89f27cc925390160dc0ec1bd37e
(Not sure how much the added `new Map(...)` affects performance.)

issue.title: QueryClient in react-query is not a constructor when built without `--no-scope-hoist`
issue.body:
<!---
Thanks for filing an issue 😄 ! Before you submit, please read the following:

Search open/closed issues before submitting since someone might have asked the same thing before!
-->

# 🐛 bug report

I built this code without `--no-scope-hoist`

```sh
$ parcel build public/index.html
```

```ts
import { QueryClient } from "react-query";

export const queryClient = new QueryClient({
  defaultOptions: {
    queries: {
      retry: false,
      staleTime: 30_000,
    },
  },
});
```

I got an error

```
Uncaught TypeError: u(...).QueryClient is not a constructor
    at Object.<anonymous> (queryClient.ts:3)
    at u (index.c2e4b2d4.js:1)
    at Object.<anonymous> (index.c2e4b2d4.js:1)
    at u (index.c2e4b2d4.js:1)
    at errorMap.ts:64
```

look at the bundle file, the implementation looks like this

```ts
// probably double-registered react-query
s.register("1ePuM", (function(t, r) {
    e(t.exports, "QueryClientProvider", (()=>s("agerD").QueryClientProvider)),
    e(t.exports, "QueryClient", (()=>s("gFcsm").QueryClient)),
    e(t.exports, "useQueryClient", (()=>s("agerD").useQueryClient)),
    e(t.exports, "useQuery", (()=>s("agerD").useQuery)),
    e(t.exports, "QueryClientProvider", (()=>s("2zDpH").QueryClientProvider)),
    e(t.exports, "QueryClient", (()=>s("7bglC").QueryClient)),
    e(t.exports, "useQueryClient", (()=>s("2zDpH").useQueryClient)),
    e(t.exports, "useQuery", (()=>s("gMHw0").useQuery)),
    s("cFtTt")
}
)),

// gFcsm contains the implementation
s.register("gFcsm", (function(t, r) {
    e(t.exports, "QueryClient", (()=>f));
    var n = s("1866z")
    // ...
})),

// but 7bglC is empty function...
s.register("7bglC", (function(e, t) {}
)),
```

## 🤔 Expected Behavior

react-query must be bundled without being overwritten by an empty function 🤔 

## 🌍 Your Environment

| Software         | Version(s) |
| ---------------- | ---------- |
| Parcel           | 2.0.0
| Node             | 14.18.1
| npm/Yarn         | yarn 1.22.17
| Operating System | MacOS 11.6, ubuntu-latest

issue.title: Entry referenced in script tag is being processed twice since v2
issue.body:
# 🐛 bug report

We have a JS file containing deployment configurations that needs to have a static name, so that we can replace the file on the server after building, which worked normally in Pacel v1 by passing the static file as an entry:

```parcel build index.html should_have_static_filename.js``` 

Since v2, this doesn't work anymore and the file is processed twice as described in "Current behavior"

## 🎛 Configuration (.babelrc, package.json, cli command)

package.json:
```
{
  "name": "vanilla",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "JavaScript example starter project",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "parcel index.html should_have_static_filename.js --open",
    "build": "parcel build index.html should_have_static_filename.js"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "parcel": "^2.8.3"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@babel/core": "7.2.0",
    "typescript": "4.4.4"
  },
  "resolutions": {
    "@babel/preset-env": "7.13.8"
  },
  "keywords": [
    "javascript",
    "starter"
  ]
}
```

## 🤔 Expected Behavior

`should_have_static_filename.js` is just copied to the dist folder. Parcel recognizes the reference in `index.html` and leaves it untouched.

## 😯 Current Behavior

Given the files:
```
- index.html
- should_have_static_filename.js
```

with `index.html` containing:

```
(...)
<script src="should_have_static_filename.js></script>
(...)
```
```parcel build index.html should_have_static_filename.js``` 
processes `should_have_static_filename.js` twice:
- Once for the entry passed to the build script, copying it to the dist as expected
- and once for the reference inside `index.html` transforming and renaming it to have the hashed filename.

So in the end, we have two versions of `should_have_static_filename.js` and the reference in `index.html` is pointing to the wrong file.

## 🔦 Context

We really need the file to keep a static name for deployment.

After many hours of trying, we made it work like this: https://github.com/codecentric/single-page-application-server/tree/master/examples/react-parcel but it just seems wrong that we need to extra plugins for a use case this common.

## 💻 Code Sample

[CodeSandbox](https://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/intelligent-pine-9tqs61?file=%2Fpackage.json%3A7%2C15-7%2C69)

## 🌍 Your Environment

| Software         | Version(s) |
| ---------------- | ---------- |
| Parcel           | 2.8.3 |
| Node             | 18.12.1 |
| npm/Yarn         | 8.19.2

<!-- Love parcel? Please consider supporting our collective:
👉  https://opencollective.com/parcel/donate -->
